</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usiryakk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sir Yakk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/10/02 11:12:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=641.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> So, a few flaws:<br>
<br>
Specialization effects.<br>
<br>
Med tick missing chance based off casting time of spell (ie, on combat medding).  Looks like the chance is 50% in your table?  This is a factor of ManaburnPS, basically.<br>
<br>
The &quot;minutes&quot; are in &quot;minutes per hour engaged&quot; right?  <br>
<br>
Your item calculations are a bit wonkey.  You need a MPS (mana per second = Cost/CT) figure to work out exactly how much time one has to use the items.<br>
<br>
Then<br>
ItemTime = BattleTime - TotalMana/MPS<br>
is a reasonably accurate measure of how much time is spent on item nuking.<br>
<br>
(it fails in extreme cases, however -- as ItemTime gets close to 0, wierd effects occur if you don't use the Grim Aura trick.)<br>
<br>
Lets assume that once you nuke, you don't sit down.  Then, you end up with a slightly different ManaburnPS (it is Mana/(CT + 2.5)).  The time you spend standing (in theory) in an hour is:<br>
<br>
StandingTime(ticks) = ManaGainedInHour / MPTick<br>
<br>
ManaGainedInHour = 600 * (ManaRegenEffects + 1) + (600 - StandingTime) * (MeddingRegen - 1)<br>
<br>
(The + 1 is for idle regen, the -1 is to cancel out the + 1 that was already counted in the first half of the equation)<br>
<br>
<br>
We care about ManaGainedInHour, so we have:<br>
<br>
MGH = 600 * (MRE + 1) + (600 - MGH/MPT) (MR - 1)<br>
<br>
MGH = 600 * MRE + 600 + 600 * MR - 600 - (MGH/MPT)*(MR -1)<br>
<br>
MGH + (MGH/MPT)*(MR - 1) = 600 * (MRE + MR)<br>
<br>
MGH * ((MR - 1)/MPT + 1) = 600 * (MRE + MR)<br>
MGH = 600 * (MRE + MR) / ((MR-1)/MPT + 1)<br>
<br>
Now, Ice Spear and Sundering have a MPT of 360 (I didn't sit down between them).<br>
<br>
MR is 20.16, so we have . . .<br>
<br>
<br>
600 * (26.5 + 20.16) / ((19.16)/360 + 1)<br>
<br>
Or about 21050 mana per hour.<br>
<br>
At a ratio around 3.9 &amp; 90% efficient, we get. . .<br>
<br>
20.52 DPS over the hour, irrespective of the engagmement % really.<br>
<br>
Now, let E be an efficiency increase, and Y be a MPT decrease.<br>
<br>
27.0 * E / (19.16/(360*Y) + 1)<br>
<br>
is your DPS.  Ie, with insta-casts (never missing a tick), you are doing 27.0 ish DPS.<br>
<br>
Make Y be .1 (burn mana 10 times slower).  Let E be 1.5 (burn mana 50% faster).  No change in DPS.<br>
<br>
Let Y be 1/6, and E be 2.  DPS only goes up by 1.5.<br>
<br>
Toss in an item with a DPS of R.<br>
<br>
ItemTime = (EnagementTime - NukeTime)<br>
ItemDamage = ItemTime * R<br>
ManaLostToItem = ItemTime * 19.16/6<br>
DamageLostToItem = 11.18 * ItemTime<br>
<br>
NetDamageCausedByItem = (R - 11.18) * (EngagmentTime-NukeTime)<br>
<br>
Now, R is 47.04 for a Robe of Invocation.  So, we get a net swing of 35.86 DPS for every second you use it.  =)  Well, not quite, not that easy.<br>
<br>
See, less medding = less MPH = less nuke time = more item time = less medding.  =)<br>
<br>
Luckily, MPH is much easier to calculate if you are chain-using an item.  It is simply<br>
<br>
MGH = 600 * (37 + 20.16 - EngagementPercent * 19.16)<br>
= 28.2 k - 11.5 k * EngagementTime/3600<br>
<br>
NukeTime = MGH/MPS = MGH / (60*Y)<br>
= 60 * (7.8 - 3.2 * ET / 3600) / Y<br>
<br>
And, NukingDPS under this model is:<br>
NDPS = E * MGH / 1000<br>
or so.  And<br>
IDPS = ItemDamage / 3600<br>
<br>
Thus, total DPS is:<br>
DPS = IDPS + NDPS<br>
= (35.86 * (ET - NT))/3600 + MGH / 1000<br>
~= <br>
(ET - 60 * (7.8 - 3.2 * ET / 3600) / Y) / 100) &gt;&gt; IDPS +<br>
E * (28.2 - 11.5 * ET/3600)<br>
~=<br>
((ET - ET/(20*Y) )/100 - 4.68) &gt;&gt; IDPS +<br>
28.2 * E - 11.5 * E * ET/3600<br>
~=<br>
ET/100 - ET/2000Y - 4.68 + 28.2 * E - E * ET / 327<br>
~= (assume Y = E = 1)<br>
ET/80 + 23.5<br>
<br>
So, for a 20 minute battle, we have a spell+item DPS of:<br>
38.5 DPS<br>
40 minites per hour:<br>
53.5 DPS<br>
<br>
Which matches them with rogues in 33% (20 minute) hours, and warriors in 66% (40 minute) hours.<br>
<br>
